    <p class="text-gray-300">The linear trick consists of also ignoring equations (9) and (10), not creating variables nor constraints for wires  <span class="math">y_i</span>  and  <span class="math">c_i</span>  for any  <span class="math">i \\in [w-1]</span> . (Note that we must keep a variable for  <span class="math">c_w</span> , which is the input to an S-box.) This way, the constraints modelling a pair of partial rounds can be reduced to:</p>

